history.content: I would say that 161 and 162 would pair up well. 168 is a comparatively chill class while I've heard that 152 has a heavy workload.

Hello. Next semester I am taking CS 162 and Data 100, as well as a breadth class. Additionally, I'm trying to choose between 152, 161, and 168, both in terms of how well their workload would balance with 162 and C100 (since 162 is known to be a workload-heavy class), as well as their importance and relevance in the industry.

Some more info about me:

I'm currently a Junior in EECS, and have taken all lower div EE and CS courses, as well as 170, 188, and 186.

I really enjoyed 61c, so I'm interested in learning more in 152, but I'm also very interested in 161, and somewhat interested in 168. However, I've heard that 168 has the easiest workload of the three, so this might pair well with taking Operating Systems.

What would you suggest I take?
history.subject: Choosing between 152/161/168. What should I take?
